<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-07-16T10:45:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-07-16T10:45:00-05:00" n="895" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d895">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">817.00 Bandit Activities, 1931/192:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Hanna</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-07-16T10:00:00-05:45">July 16, 1931—10
                                a.m.</date><lb/>[Received 8:40 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>139. Supplementing my 137, July 13, 4 p.m.,<note n="24" xml:id="d895fn24">Not printed.</note> there have been persistent rumors for some days
                            of a considerable bandit movement towards the east coast. The Guardia is
                            endeavoring to develop the situation and the air forces are
                            cooperating.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hanna</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>